               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20110518"/>
            </section>
         </component>
         <component>
            <section ID="d2">
               <id root="d226c570-ab6c-4730-a0bf-1b89c6db5aac"/>
               <code code="51945-4" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="PACKAGE LABEL.PRINCIPAL DISPLAY PANEL"/>
               <title>Label –
</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>NDC 54868-4793-1<br/>
                  </paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <renderMultiMedia referencedObject="mm03"/>
                  </paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Restasis
</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="italics">(Cyclosporine Ophthalmic Emulsion) 0.05%</content>
                  </paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="bold">30 Single-Use Vials (0.4 mL each) <br/>
                     </content>
                  </paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="bold">Each mL contains: Active:</content> cyclosporine 0.05% <content styleCode="bold">Inactives:</content> glycerin; castor oil; polysorbate 80; carbomer copolymer type A; purified water; and sodium hydroxide to adjust the pH. <content styleCode="bold">Usual Dosage:</content> Twice daily approximately 12 hours apart. Invert the vial before using. Use immediately after opening and then discard.
</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="bold">Note:</content> Store at 15 - 25° C (59 - 77° F). Store vials in the thermoformed tray until use. The entire contents of each package (60 vials) must be dispensed intact.
</paragraph>
                  <content styleCode="bold">Rx only</content>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20110518"/>
